19/02/2008
WASHINGTON, United States -- Defence ministers of countries in the Adriatic Charter group visit Washington on Tuesday (February 19th) for a meeting with US Defence Secretary Robert Gates. 
Macedonian Defence Minister Lazar Elenovski, his Albanian counterpart, Fatmir Mediu, and Croatia's Branko Vukelic will exchange views and experiences regarding preparations for NATO's April summit in Bucharest. 
They are expected to issue a joint statement on successful co-operation within the US-Adriatic Charter. 
Discussion topics are expected to include Army reforms as a prerequisite for NATO membership, joint military exercises and participation in the international security mission in Afghanistan. 
(Makfax, MIA - 19/02/08)
